    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-19T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-19T08:00:00-05:00" n="103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-19T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 19, 1918—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 20—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2380. The press states that the President and the Secretary of State are on their
                    way to Paris. Learn also from members of Ministry here that they are informed
                    from Paris that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName> is coming to
                    Europe. If he comes, he will be expected to visit Italy.</p>
                <p>Both the <persName>King</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_OVE1"
                        >Orlando</persName> have expressed great pleasure that he is coming and
                    their belief that it be of great importance in enabling him to understand many
                    problems.</p>
                <p>His failure to visit Italy would have unfortunate and possibly serious effect
                    upon our relations and would greatly increase existing tension between France
                    and Italy.</p>
                <p>Everyone here desirous of doing him all honor and all questions affecting
                    official visits easily adjustable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
